<h2>Information for performers</h2>
<p>
    <i>NB: We'll have a proper FAQ up here soon. Meanwhile please enjoy this earlier version of the email we send to performers prior to the show</i>
</p>

<p>Hi!</p>

<p>
This email is for performers who have registered to play the November edition of emom.sydney.  
Super great to have you on board if you're new, great to have you back if not!
</p>

<p>
Please read the following information carefully, it will help the smooth running of the event if
everyone is on the same page.
</p>

<p>
My name is Stewart and I'll be your guide on this adventure. I'm working in partnership with the
crew at Mothership to make it a fun, inclusive and entertaining night for audience and performers
alike. In that vein here are a few notes on what to expect, and what we need from our performers
in order for everything to run like clockwork.
</p>

<h2>Arrival</h2>

<p>
We're asking everyone to arrive at or before <strong>6pm</strong>, so we have time to get organised before doors
open. Entrance to the building is via the drive/laneway to the right of Mothership's official front
door. Our lovely door staff will be there to guide you in. Once everyone is present and accounted
for, we'll have a quick huddle to decide on the running order.
</p>

<h2>Schedule</h2>

<p><strong>Doors open:</strong> 6:30pm<br>
<strong>First act starts:</strong> 7:00pm sharp</p>

<p>
This time around we're trying a slightly different format. Instead of each act having a 15‑minute
set then a 15‑minute break to change over, we're going to set up two acts at a time — one on a
fixed table and one on a wheeled table. The first act of the pair will use the wheeled table, then
we can roll it out of the way and have the second act start almost immediately.
</p>

<p>
Then there will be an interval break, hopefully no longer than 10–15 minutes, while the next two
acts set up.
</p>

<h2>Technical Setup</h2>

<p>
Each table will have its own powerboard and DI boxes. We ask that you bring everything you need
to provide a <strong>stereo line‑level mix</strong> for the PA. The DIs have <strong>1/4" (6.5mm) jack inputs</strong>, and it helps
enormously if you can just give our stage‑hand a pair of jack cables with your mix to plug in.
</p>

<p>
If you have vocals, we have an SM58 microphone available. If you're able to mix your own vocals
through your own submixer, that may be preferable if you have a particular sound in mind.
</p>

<p>
Bear in mind that we don't have time to do a full soundcheck — it'll just be a quick level/line check.
That said, it's very important to keep an eye on your mix levels and avoid overdriving our inputs!
</p>

<h2>Recording & Live Streaming</h2>

<p>
We will be set up to record the night and hopefully live stream as well. If you don't want to be
recorded that's ok — just let us know beforehand. I send out links for you to access all the
recordings of your set as soon as possible in the days following.
</p>

<h2>Final Notes</h2>

<p>
If you have any other questions or concerns, shoot me an email — otherwise we'll see you at
<strong>6pm on the dot on Thursday</strong>!  
(<em>Mothership Studios @ 22 Sydney St Marrickville</em>)
</p>

<p>
<strong>PS:</strong> If for some reason you're going to be unable to make it on the night, please text me at any
time. I'd rather know we have a space to fill in advance than discover there's a space we could
have filled if only we'd known!
</p>
